FBIS4-65045 "drweu092pr_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-092 Daily Report 11 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS UNHCR Needs Extra $236 Million for Yugoslavia Refugees UNHCR Needs Extra $236 Million for Yugoslavia Refugees AU1105134194 Paris AFP in English 1326 GMT 11 May 94 AU1105134194 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Geneva, May 11 (AFP) -- The UN High Commissioner for Refugees is short of 236 million dollars to help until year's end four million refugees from the former Yugoslavia, the agency said Wednesday [11 May]. The UNHCR said it needed a total 338 million dollars for the entire year -- or 918,000 dollars a day -- but had received only 102 million dollars from donor countries by March 31, leaving a 236-million-dollar hole. The main beneficiary of United Nations aid is Bosnia-Herzegovina, followed by Croatia.
